Reference to a `Prompt` instance `self` is not replaced with such an assignment `self = Command(func, params)` (within `command_wrapper` method), being just a local variable i that context.

Your phrase *&quot;I expect instance to refer to a `Command` object &quot;* points to the intention of using ***Delegation***.&lt;br&gt;
Define an additional field for the delegate, say `self._command = None` (within `Prompt` constructor).&lt;br&gt;
Modify `command_wrapper` to set a delegate `self._command = Command(func, params)`.&lt;br&gt;
Change `quit` method to destroy the internal *command* window:

    def quit(self):
       self._command.window.destroy()

But, to eventually destroy the initial *prompt* instance window you&#39;d have to call it directly: `prompt_instance.window.destroy()`.

